{"word":"H170 - אׇהֳלָה - ʼOhŏlâh - o-hol-aw' - Aholah","slug":"H170","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אׇהֳלָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼOhŏlâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>o-hol-aw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Aholah"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D0;&#x05D4;&#x05DC;&#x05D4;&#x05BC;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&#x05D0;&#x05D4;&#x05DC;&#x05D4; - 'oho&#x0306;la&#x0302;h  'oho&#x0306;la&#x0302;hh</b> - <i>o-hol-aw', o-hol-aw'</i><p/>The first form is in form a feminine of <a href=\"#/H168\">H168</a>, but is in fact for the second form; from <a href=\"#/H168\">H168</a>; <i>her tent</i> (that is, idolatrous <i>sanctuary</i>); <i>Oholah</i>, a symbolic name for Samaria: - Aholah."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H167\">H167</a>, <a href=\"#/H168\">H168</a>, <a href=\"#/H169\">H169</a>, <a href=\"#/H171\">H171</a>, <a href=\"#/H172\">H172</a>, <a href=\"#/H173\">H173</a>"}]}